reviews.text: We ordered food at this location during our stay at Ohio. We placed online order and it was easy to place the order and there were specials and coupons available in online too. The food was ready on time and we were able to pick up the food and it is definitely simple and convenient process.  The store is located closer to main way and has limited parking. there was plenty of tables.The interior is good for dine in.The staff is friendly and welcoming.   The food is okay. We ordered a Calzone and Veggie subs. The Calzone was okay but the subs were good. Overall its worth a try.

We were driving through on our way to Philly and stopped here for dinner. Very good pizza and I loved the bread sticks. Man, I need more bread sticks! Quick service, clean restaurant, nice employees! Definitely a wonderful place to try if you're in the area!

I went to the all you can eat buffet today and it was very good. Lots of supply of different styles of pizza and a very nice salad bar with lots of toppings.  I noticed that the waitress was very attentive to the bar and kept it clean and stocked and was very prompt on drink refills .
I will definitely be back.

I pass this place everyday on my way home from work and always thought of giving it a try. My coworker came in today with pizza from DeFelice and I was immediately sold upon seeing it.

On my way home from work today, I called DeFelice numerous times for a pick up order with no one picking up. It was 5:00 p.m. so I knew they were busy. I called again around 6:30, I was hung up on trying one last time before giving up. An employee finally answered this time.

I ordered a sausage and pepperoni pizza and was told it'd be ready in 45 minutes.
I went and picked up my pizza eating it in the dining room.

The pizza looks way better than it actually tastes. It's the blandest, most flavorless pizza I've ever had in my whole entire life. It was the very first time I've ever put salt on that pizza to add flavor which says a whole lot. üò¨

The slices are huge, fulfilling and nourishing. I was starving so at least it made me full

While dining, I overheard one of the obvious longtime employees complaining about the 5pm dinner rush and how she just lets the phone just ring instead of answering. I was so turned off after hearing this because I figured that's what was going on earlier when my calls went unanswered. üò§

There was another young employee there who I think was her first day on the job. She was a complete sweetheart and did an amazing job serving the customers. You rock!

This was an unsatisfying experience and I won't be back. You are much better off going to Pizza Hut down the road.

Great plate of pasta. I got mine with meatballs, some extra sauce, a little parmesean, and a side of bambino bread. For a short time I was the King of Clairsville. Those cookies they sell by the register are top notch too, I'd love to come back and try some more, God bless.

editorial_summary.overview: Family-friendly spot for specialty & custom pizza, subs, calzones & design-your-own pasta.

detailedReviews.author: Sarah Catling
detailedReviews.text:
Food is inconsistent. It is never the same, the pasta is dry, pizza comes delivered cold, delivery time is well over an hour. We ordered for Valentines day, I understand it was busy, but the customer service was horrible. We were told we would have a credit for our food. Called back to use it and the owner was rude and disrespectful,  pretty much said we were lying to her. They have lost our business. We have watched, through the drive thru window, their employees eat out of containers and blatantly ignore customers. Biggest downfall is the horrible customer service and the owner is right up there with them,  so I guess you learn what you are taught.

Update:
Manager did have her employee call back and try to make it right after they went back and found it. While the employee did call back the manager/owner as she called herself did not even have the courtesy to call back and talk to us herself. So we will remain ex-customers! That is horrible service!

detailedReviews.author: Amy Hendershot
detailedReviews.text:
This place used to be amazing,  but after waiting almost an hour for salad and a pizza,  I'm ready to give up!  The server was prompt and courteous, but she can't control the kitchen,  and they were SLOW.

Edit:  After receiving our food, it was absolutely delicious and worth every minute of the wait!

Second edit:  I asked the server for a glass of ice water to drink with my food and she never brought it.  The food still so yummy that it was worth it, but it would have been nice to have something to drink with my meal.

detailedReviews.author: Matt
detailedReviews.text:
If you like a thicker crust, you will enjoy the pizza.  We prefer thin, and their thin is pretty good - still has that crispy bottom without the carbs.  Plenty of sauce, cheese, and toppings.
We don't get to St C often, so we were a little disappointed they were out of thin crust (how does a pizza place run out of crust?) on our last order.  Only real complaint was waiting at the drive thru window for five minutes before somebody walked up.

detailedReviews.text: The pepperoni rolls are terrible! They taste pre-made no flavor they taste like garbage I will never give my business to them again.

detailedReviews.text: So this is the biggest and baddest of the DBP locations and i agree its the best but i think its more cause it has more of that great defelice crust smell then other smaller locations but the pizza across all locations is great and consistent so they are all winners. Thing with this one is its got all the bells and whistles so give it a try along with your local shop.

detailedReviews.author: Lee Donnell
detailedReviews.text: Spent over $80 and waited close to an hour and the order wasn't right, at all. Didn't know it until we got home. My fault for not checking. The pizza and bread sticks were undercooked. Ordered 3 heart pizzas but was given 1 heart and the rest regular. Was very overcrowded inside with a very long line. The parking lot is extremely cramped. Almost got rear ended try to pull out.The workers there are not professional at all. If you ask them a question they will tell you that they don't know, then won't follow up. And don't bother trying to call them. It rang for 12 minutes before I hung up. All in all this establishment isn't very good.

detailedReviews.author: Addie S
detailedReviews.text: Loved DeFelice for many years, excited to be living back in the delivery area always lived the calzones and are as excellent as they were over 10 years ago, tried the Diavolo today first time, it's now a favorite also! And the delivery  driver I've had the last few times is great!

detailedReviews.author: Jacqueline Lindow
detailedReviews.text: The service is a bit hectic! To say the least ! The worst service I have ever gotten anywhere!! The kids working here are not real knowledgeable of the menu . Therefore if you are asking questions about the menu..... They have to look at menu or ask someone who then has to ask someone else and so on. Delivery orders take a long time. Way longer then how long they say it will be. They rarely bring napkins or silverware and 3 out of 5 times the good was not hot. The food is excellent though! It's nice that they hire young kids but they need to have an experienced adult on all shifts as well!

detailedReviews.author: Olan Teague
detailedReviews.text:
Atmosphere is just a 3 star for me saying I don't know  everytime I come in its about 30 minutes befote close. So I have no reference

Service as mentioned a lot of high school people it seems at the counter knowledge on the low side but they are always friendly good folks.

Food comment below my Texas run-on below,

Me- work up here occasionally from Texas.  In Texas some local places but the market is dominated really by the big 3-4 matinal chains then of course several other national but small foot print chains.  Mom and pops style places kinda rare besides major cities, or local small town places usually offering wings and bread with spaghetti sauce on it. Up here though many local small regional chains.  With a wide variety of pizza styles and offerings.
In st Clairsville I have had 3-4 different places.  These guys are my go to.  Diverse menu without of good items.  Never had a bad " new food" experience here.  Not gonna say it's some gourmet experience but the food is ways working man good solid stuff. This is a small local chain.  I have expeeienced in other towns around the are they have all been solid choices as well.

Just keep in mind, back home we have lots of BBQ chicken and Taco places, up here sandwiches and Italian food tend to regin Supreme.

The food
I get now default to, the " Supreme" everything pizza, as others mentioned it is sorta ( Crust pizza hut like), price $20 ish for the large  but it is good... the toppings the toppings these guys do not skimp the pizza is loaded with meat or veggies --both- flavors very good stuff. In fact  I usualy scarpe the toppings of two slices, save it and mix Into a can of tomato soup, and air fry the crust for a great meal later in the week, I gradients taste crunch feel fresh and not cheep.  Sauce not bad,

Sandwiches I have had about 4 different ones all top notch. Good meat great prices.
Wings are wings to me but these are good.
The appetizers the sausage and peppers In sauce nearly a meal on  its own.  That and a sandwich you have supper for two days easy.

Iove the food here, and it's value I promise you will not eat this well and feel your dollars are respected anywhere else In town. Between the food and price your stealing and " getting away with it" .

detailedReviews.author: Carol Brunner
detailedReviews.text: Ordered a thin crust pizza tonight. The crust was perfect, the sauce authentic and it had generous quality toppings. Reasonably priced. Will definitely order the next time we pass through St. Clairsville

detailedReviews.author: Lou Tag
detailedReviews.text: Pizza is awesome! High schoolers running the register was not so good. They had issues with taking the order. We ended up ordering something we didn't necessarily want, however to get an order placed we just did it. Where was the manager... Sitting in a booth!!!

detailedReviews.author: Wes Cornett
detailedReviews.text: Good pizza. Really really good pizza

detailedReviews.author: Rick Murray
detailedReviews.text:
We was looking for a pizza eat in restaurant, we aren't from the area. Of course I googled and looked at many places to eat and just happened to see DeFelice.

We parked, went inside and found they had a pizza buffet and salad bar. We asked how long was the Buffet open. We were told it was open for about 30 minutes more. We hurried up and all of us enjoyed the salad bar and buffet.

The waitress was nice and said she was going to get a few more pizzas made for us to enjoy. Very nice of them.

The pizza buffet and salad bar were both really good, the waitress was very nice and attentive to what we needed like drinks and such.

The pizza crust to me seemed similar to a pizza hut crust which I like and the pizza sauce was a nice rich pizza sauce which I also like.

Thank you,
The Murray's
